    <h1>CFO AI Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><small>Effective date: April 22, 2026</small></p>

    <p>CFO AI provides accounting workflow, automation, and finance operations
  support for businesses.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect account information, business information, integration
  metadata, accounting data, transaction data, and technical logs necessary to
  operate the application.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>We use information to provide the application, authenticate users,
  connect integrations, process accounting workflows, maintain security,
  troubleshoot issues, and improve reliability.</p>

    <h2>QuickBooks Data</h2>
    <p>QuickBooks data is used to operate the application and provide requested
  functionality. It is not used to train general-purpose machine learning or
  generative AI models.</p>

    <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell customer data. We may share data with service providers
  and integration partners only as necessary to operate the application and
  deliver requested features.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational
  safeguards designed to protect data and credentials from unauthorized access,
  use, or disclosure.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain data for as long as necessary to provide the service, comply
  with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.</p>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>
    <p>You may request disconnection of integrations and request account-
  related assistance by contacting us.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time by posting an
  updated version on this page.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy questions, contact: <a
  href="mailto:notchin4@gmail.com">notchin4@gmail.com</a></p>
